description: One of the three parts of the spinalis muscle, which takes its origin from the spinous processes of the upper thoracic vertebrae, and which inserts into the spinous processes of the eleventh and twelfth thoracic and first and second lumbar vertebrae; it functions to support and extend the vertebral column.
label: Spinalis Thoracis

description: A group of muscles causing movement of the leg towards the midline of the body.
label: Adductor Group of the Leg

description: A group of muscles including the biceps femoris, semimembranosus and semitendinosus that extend down the back of the thigh.
label: Hamstring

description: A muscle originating from the transverse processes of the lower thoracic vertebrae which inserts into the ribs between the angles and tubercles as well as the transverse and accessory processes of the upper lumbar vertebrae acting to extend the spine.
label: Longissimus Thoracis

description: The more superficial of the two muscles (peroneus longus and peroneus brevis) of the lateral compartment of the lower leg, which originates at the superior, lateral shaft of the fibula and inserts on the first metatarsal and the medial cuneiform, functioning to plantar flex and evert the foot, and which supports the lateral, longitudinal, and transverse arches.
label: Peroneus Longus

description: Two sets of interossei muscles (dorsal and plantar) that run along the metatarsal bones in the foot controlling the movement of the toes.
label: Foot Interosseous Muscle

description: Four muscles in the foot between the metatarsal bones extending down the medial and lateral sides of the proximal phalanx of the second toe and the lateral side of the proximal phalanx on the third and fourth toe.
label: Dorsal Foot Interosseous Muscle

description: A dorsal interosseous muscle of the foot that originates on the lateral side of the first metatarsal and the medial side of the second metatarsal, and inserts into the medial side of the base of the proximal phalanx of the second toe.
label: First Dorsal Interosseous Muscle of the Foot

description: Three small muscles located on the medial aspect of the third, fourth, and fifth metatarsal bones that facilitate adduction of the toes.
label: Plantar Foot Interosseus Muscle

description: Two sets of interossei muscles (dorsal and palmar) that run along the metacarpal bones in the hand controlling the movement of the fingers.
label: Hand Interosseous Muscle

description: Four muscles in the hand between the metacarpal bones originating on the radial side of the metacarpal as well as the ulnar side of the previous metacarpal. The second and third interosseous muscles are inserted into the third proximal phalanx while the first is inserted into the second proximal phalanx and the fourth is inserted into the fourth proximal phalanx. These muscles act to abduct the fingers away from the middle finger.
label: Dorsal Hand Interosseous Muscle

description: A muscle located at the posterior and medial aspect of the thigh that extends the hip joint, flexes the knee joint and assists in medially rotating the knee. (CDISC)
label: Semitendinosus

description: A muscle of the anterior thoracic wall originating on the posterior inferior portion of the sternum and the xiphoid process with insertion on the deep surface of costal cartilages 2-6; it functions to draw the ribs downward.
label: Transversus Thoracis

description: The detrusor muscle of the bladder, forming the muscular wall of the bladder, consisting of the inner longitudinal; middle circular; and outer longitudinal layers.
label: Muscularis Propria

description: Any of the skeletal muscles that form the buttocks. These muscles are responsible for hip abduction and extension as well as movement of the thigh.
label: Gluteal Muscle

description: The outermost and largest muscle of the buttocks.
label: Gluteus Maximus

description: One of the three gluteal muscles on the lateral surface of the pelvic bone that abducts and rotates the thigh.
label: Gluteus Medius

description: One of the three gluteal muscles on the lateral surface of the pelvic bone that abducts and rotates the thigh located on the left side of the body.
label: Left Gluteus Medius

description: One of the three gluteal muscles on the lateral surface of the pelvic bone that abducts and rotates the thigh located on the right side of the body.
label: Right Gluteus Medius

description: A muscle located close to the trunk of the body.
label: Proximal Muscle

description: A muscle located away from the trunk of the body.
label: Distal Muscle

description: The anterior portion of the head extending from the forehead to the chin and ear to ear. The facial structures contain the eyes, nose and mouth, cheeks and jaws.
label: Face

description: A sheet or band of fibrous connective tissue enveloping, separating, or binding together muscles, organs, and other soft structures of the body.
label: Fascia

description: A fibrous connective tissue covering the kidney and adrenal gland, which separates the perinephric fat from paranephric fat.
label: Gerota Fascia

description: The dense fibroconnective tissue layer separating the vagina and rectum. It contains the inferior hypogastric plexus and serves to stabilize the pelvic wall. The rectovesical septum (Denonvilliers fascia) is the male homolog.
label: Rectovaginal Septum

description: list()
label: Deep Fascia

description: list()
label: Deep Palmar Fascia

description: list()
label: Fascia Lata

description: list()
label: Intercostal Fascia

description: list()
label: Plantar Fascia

description: list()
label: Palmar Fascia

description: list()
label: Superficial Fascia

description: The Muscle Spindle is composed of intrafusal fibers that are located within and run parallel to the extrafusal fibers of skeletal muscle. When the extrafusal fibers are stretched, the intrafusal fibers of the spindle stretch as well. When stretching occurs, the sensory neuron from the muscle spindle signals the motor neurons located within the ventral horn of the spinal cord. This signal causes the motor neurons to fire, resulting in contraction of the muscle. This reflex arc provides negative feedback. The muscular contraction induced by the stretching works against or negates further muscle stretch. This mechanism helps to maintain proper muscle tension or tone. Although the muscle spindle helps to maintain proper muscle tension, unlike the Golgi tendon organ, it is not an indicator of muscle tension, but rather of muscle length.
label: Muscle Spindle

description: The larger of two heads of the adductor hallucis muscle. It originates from the sheath of the peroneus longus tendon and the plantar surface of the bases of the second to fourth metatarsal bones in the foot.
label: Oblique Head of Adductor Hallucis Muscle

description: The smaller of two heads of the adductor hallucis muscle. It originates from the deep transverse metatarsal ligament and the plantar surface of the metatarsophalangeal joints of the lateral three toes.
label: Transverse Head of Adductor Hallucis Muscle

description: One of two heads of the gastrocnemius muscle, originating on the lateral femoral condyle.
label: Lateral Head of Gastrocnemius Muscle

description: One of two heads of the gastrocnemius muscle, originating on the medial femoral condyle.
label: Medial Head of Gastrocnemius Muscle

description: A flat, tendon-like membrane that serves to bind muscles or to attach muscles to bones.
label: Aponeurosis

description: A band of fibrous connective tissue that joins bone to muscle.
label: Tendon

description: The tendons located on the palm side of the fingers that connect the flexor muscles of the forearm and hand to bones in the fingers, enabling flexion towards the palm.
label: Finger Flexor Tendons

description: The tendons located on the dorsal side of the fingers that connect muscles of the forearm and hand to bones in the fingers, enabling straightening of the fingers.
label: Finger Extensor Tendons

description: The tendons located along the inside of the forearm that cross at the wrist and connect muscles of the forearm to wrist and hand bones, enabling bending of the wrist towards the palm.
label: Wrist Joint Flexor Tendons

description: The tendons located along the back part of the forearm that cross to the thumb side of the wrist and connect muscles of the forearm to the base of hand bones, enabling bending of the wrist back and towards the thumb.
label: Wrist Joint Extensor Tendons

description: The tendons that connect the muscles and bones that comprise the glenohumeral and acromioclavicular joints and enable abduction of the arm and stabilization of the shoulder.
label: Shoulder Joint Tendons

description: The tendons that connect the quadriceps muscles to the kneecap, the hamstring muscles to the shin bone and fibula, and the patella to the top part of the fibula, enabling flexion, extension, and slight rotation of the knee.
label: Knee Joint Tendons

description: A fibrous band extending from the distal end of the quadriceps femoris to the top of the patella.
label: Patellar Tendon

description: The tendons in the anterior compartment of the leg that connect muscles that originate on the surfaces of the femur, tibia, and fibula to bones in the toes and enable plantar flexion of the foot at the ankle.
label: Ankle Joint Anterior Flexor Tendons

description: The tendons in the anterior compartment of the leg that cross the tibiotalar joint anteriorly and connect muscles that originate on the surfaces of the tibia and fibula to bones in the toes and enable dorsiflexion of the foot at the ankle and extension of the toes.
label: Ankle Joint Anterior Extensor Tendons

description: The tendon that connects the heel bone to the calf muscles at the back of the lower leg.
label: Achilles Tendon

description: The longitudinal fiber of the esophagus connected to the cricoid cartilage of the larynx.
label: Cricoesophageal Tendon

description: list()
label: Endomysium

description: list()
label: Epimysium

description: A muscle fiber that is able to hydrolyze ATP and transmit electrochemical signals rapidly.
label: Fast-twitch Motor Unit

description: Fibrillar protein polymers found in the contractile apparatus of muscle cells.
label: Myofilament

description: A myofilament composed of myosin.
label: Thick Filament

description: A myofilament composed of actin and tropomyosin.
label: Thin Filament

description: A dense connective tissue sheath surrounding a bundle of muscle fibers.
label: Perimysium

description: A membrane-lined sac that is located in a joint, and is filled with synovial fluid; it provides a cushion between bones and tendons and/or muscles, decreasing the friction between two moving structures and allowing for unrestricted movement.
label: Synovial Bursa

description: A long, cylindrical, multinucleated cell comprising a network of myofibrils, which contain several proteins that compose the contractile unit of skeletal muscle, of which there are three basic types: intermediate, red, and white.
label: Skeletal Fiber

description: A type of striated skeletal muscle fiber that contracts slowly and contains high amounts of mitochondria, myoglobin and sarcoplasm.
label: Red Fiber

description: A type of striated skeletal muscle fiber that contracts quicker than a red fiber but slower than a white fiber and contains only a moderate amount of mitochondria, myoglobin and sarcoplasm.
label: Intermediate Fiber

description: A type of striated skeletal muscle fiber that contracts quickly and contains small amounts of mitochondria, myoglobin and sarcoplasm.
label: White Fiber

description: A type of motor unit, comprising a group of individual muscle fibers that are activated by a single motor neuron, that has low contraction strength, high endurance, and is dependent on aerobic metabolism for energy.
label: Slow-Twitch Motor Unit

description: Any component of the framework, including bone and cartilage, that supports and/or protects the soft tissues of vertebrate animals.
label: Skeletal System Part

description: The bony prominence of the lower part of the ischium.
label: Ischial Tuberosity

description: The prominence on the lateral surface of the sacrum, posterior to the auricular surface of the sacrum.
label: Sacral Tuberosity

description: A radiolucent and fracture-prone triangular zone in the proximal femur.
label: Ward's Triangle

description: A bony projection arising from the posterior vertebral arch that serves for the attachment of muscles and ligaments.
label: Spinous Process

description: The spinous process of the 5th lumbar vertebra.
label: Fifth Lumbar Spinous Process

description: A rectangular socket or bony arch that connects the ends of the tibia and fibula to the talus.
label: Ankle Mortise

description: The elongated bony body of a fibula compressing of the anterior, posterior, internal and external surfaces separated by the anteroexternal, anterointernal, posteroexternal and posterointernal borders.
label: Fibular Shaft

description: The cylindrical, elongated bony body of a humerus compressing of the anterior, posterior and external surfaces separated by the anterior, posterior and interosseous borders. The distal portion of the shaft becomes more prismatic and flattened.
label: Humeral Shaft

description: The slightly curved, prismoid, elongated bony body of a radius compressing of the anterior, posterior and external surfaces separated by the anterior, posterior and interosseous borders.
label: Radius Shaft

description: The triangular prismoid, elongated bony body of a tibia compressing of the anterior, posterior and external surfaces separated by the anterior, posterior and interosseous borders.
label: Tibial Shaft

description: The prismatic, elongated bony body of an ulna which curves from behind forwards, and compresses of the anterior, posterior and external surfaces separated by the anterior, posterior and interosseous borders. The distal portion of the shaft is rounded, smooth and bents outward.
label: Ulnar Shaft

description: A type of connective tissue composed of chondrocytes and an extracellular matrix, composed of collagen, elastin, and ground substance. There are three types of cartilage; namely elastic, hyaline, and fibrocartilage.
label: Cartilage

description: The nine cartilages that comprise the skeleton of the larynx, including the single thyroid, epiglottic, and cricoid cartilages, and the paired arytenoid, corniculate, and cuneiform cartilages.
label: Laryngeal Cartilage

description: The largest of the laryngeal cartilages comprising two quadrilateral laminae that fuse to form a median elevation ("Adam's apple"). It lies inferior to the hyoid bone, its superior horn is attached to the tip of the greater horn of the hyoid bone, and its inferior horn articulates with the cricoid cartilage.
label: Thyroid Cartilage

description: Either of a pair of small pyramidal laryngeal cartilages that articulate with the lamina of the cricoid cartilage and give attachment to the posterior part of the corresponding vocal ligament and to several muscles.
label: Arytenoid Cartilage

description: A type of elastic cartilage that is attached to the larynx creating a flap.
label: Epiglottic Cartilage

description: One of two small conical nodules of elastic cartilage which caps the apex of the arytenoid cartilages.
label: Corniculate Cartilage

description: A cartilage ring around the trachea below the thyroid cartilage.
label: Cricoid Cartilage

description: The two small rod shaped pieces of elastic cartilage on both sides of the aryepiglottic fold which supports the epiglottis laterally and the vocal cords.
label: Cuneiform Cartilage

description: The cartilage that covers the ends of each bone in a joint.
label: Articular Cartilage

description: The cartilage positioned between the anterior end of the rib and the sternum. Its elasticity allows the ribcage to expand while breathing.
label: Costal Cartilage

description: A crescent-shaped wedge of cartilaginous material that serves as a cushion in the knee, between the tuberosities of the femur and the tibia. There are two locations, the medial meniscus located on the inner aspect of the knee and the lateral which is located on the outer aspect.
label: Meniscus

description: A semicircular meniscus located towards the outer aspect of the knee joint.
label: Meniscus Lateralis

description: A semicircular meniscus located towards the inner aspect of the knee joint.
label: Meniscus Medialis

description: A hyaline cartilage in the form of irregular rings in the larger bronchi that changes to small plates and islands in the smaller bronchi.
label: Bronchus Cartilage

description: The cartilage in the outer part of the ear.
label: External Ear Cartilage

description: The cartilage at the base of the respiratory tract.
label: Lower Respiratory Tract Cartilage

description: One of a variable number of incomplete, C-shaped cartilaginous rings encircling the anterolateral portion of the trachea, which are horizontally stacked and separated by narrow intervals throughout the length of the trachea.
label: Trachea Cartilage

description: Any of the cartilaginous structures that provide structure and support to the nose.
label: Nasal Cartilage

description: The thin wall between the two nasal cavities.
label: Nasal Septum

description: The structural organ comprised of specialized connective tissue that forms the skeletal components of the body.
label: Bone

description: Any of thirty-three ring-shaped structures that form the vertebral column which surrounds and protects the spinal cord. Each vertebra consists of a bony body with its superior and inferior articular surfaces covered by hyaline cartilage. The body includes the centrum anteriorly and vertebral arch posteriorly. The articular surfaces of the vertebrae are connected by a fibrocartilaginous intervertebral disc.
label: Vertebra

description: One of the usually five fused vertebrae forming the triangular bone just below the lumbar vertebrae.
label: Sacral Vertebra

description: The first and largest of five sacral vertebrae, which ultimately fuse into one bone: the sacrum; superiorly, it articulates with the last lumbar vertebra.
label: S1 Vertebra

description: The second of five sacral vertebrae.
label: S2 Vertebra

description: The third of five sacral vertebrae.
label: S3 Vertebra

description: The fourth of five sacral vertebrae.
label: S4 Vertebra

description: The fifth of five sacral vertebrae; it articulates with the coccyx.
label: S5 Vertebra

description: One of 12 vertebrae in the human vertebral column. The thoracic vertebrae are situated between the seventh cervical vertebra down to the first lumbar vertebra.
label: Thoracic Vertebra

description: A rare unilateral or bilateral anatomical variant in which a 13th rib-bearing vertebra is located at the thoracolumbar junction.
label: T13 Vertebra

description: The first thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T1 Vertebra

description: The tenth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T10 Vertebra

description: The eleventh thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T11 Vertebra

description: The twelfth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T12 Vertebra

description: The second thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T2 Vertebra

description: The third thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T3 Vertebra

description: The fourth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T4 Vertebra

description: The fifth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T5 Vertebra

description: The sixth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T6 Vertebra

description: The seventh thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T7 Vertebra

description: The eighth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T8 Vertebra

description: The ninth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T9 Vertebra

description: Any one of the seven vertebrae that are caudal to the skull, denoted as C1, C2, C3, C4, C5, C6 or C7.
label: Cervical Vertebra

description: The first of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C1 Vertebra

description: The second of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C2 Vertebra

description: The third of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C3 Vertebra

description: The fourth of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C4 Vertebra

description: The fifth of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C5 Vertebra

description: The sixth of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C6 Vertebra

description: The seventh of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C7 Vertebra

description: One of the five bones situated between the thoracic vertebrae and the sacrum in the lower part of the spine.
label: Lumbar Vertebra

description: The first lumbar vertebra counting from the top down.
label: L1 Vertebra

description: The second lumbar vertebra counting from the top down.
label: L2 Vertebra

description: The third lumbar vertebra counting from the top down.
label: L3 Vertebra

description: The fourth lumbar vertebra counting from the top down.
label: L4 Vertebra

description: The fifth lumbar vertebra counting from the top down.
label: L5 Vertebra

description: Four vertebral segments positioned at the base of the spine that are fused.
label: Coccygeal Vertebra

description: A bone that is comprised by the facial skeleton.
label: Maxillofacial Bone

description: The caudal portion of the trunk, bounded anteriorly and laterally by the two hip bones incorporating the socket portion of the hip joint for each leg. Posteriorly it is bounded by the sacrum and coccyx.
label: Pelvic Bone

description: The broad, dorsal, upper, and widest of the three principal bones composing either half of the pelvis.
label: Ilium

description: The most posterior and ventral bone making up the pelvis.
label: Ischium

description: Either of the two bones (left and right) that form the front of the pelvis.
label: Pubic Bone

description: The portion of the pubic ramus that lies between the superior pubic ramus and the inferior ramus of the ischium.
label: Inferior Pubic Ramus

description: The portion of the pubic ramus that lies between the body of the ilium and the inferior pubic ramus.
label: Superior Pubic Ramus

description: A bone within a limb of the body.
label: Bone of the Extremity

description: A bone of the leg (lower extremity).
label: Bone of the Lower Extremity

description: The upper leg bone positioned between the pelvis and the knee.
label: Femur

description: The small, lateral calf bone extending from the knee to the ankle.
label: Fibula

description: A bone located between the femur and the tarsus, being part of the lower leg.
label: Tibia

description: One of the seven tarsal, five metatarsal, or 14 phalangeal bones in the foot.
label: Foot Bone

description: A bone belonging to the middle part of the foot located between toes and ankle. There are 5 metatarsal bones and they are numbered from the medial side.
label: Metatarsal Bone

description: The fifth of the five long bones located in the mid-foot, which articulates proximally with the cuboid bone at the tarsometatarsal joint and distally with the metatarsophalangeal joint.
label: Metatarsal Bone Digit 5

description: The fourth of the five long bones located in the mid-foot, which articulates proximally with the cuboid and lateral cuneiform bones at the tarsometatarsal joint and distally with the metatarsophalangeal joint.
label: Metatarsal Bone Digit 4

description: The third of the five long bones located in the mid-foot, which articulates proximally with the lateral cuneiform bone at the tarsometatarsal joint and distally with the metatarsophalangeal joint.
label: Metatarsal Bone Digit 3

description: The second of the five long bones located in the mid-foot, which articulates proximally with all three cuneiform bones at the tarsometatarsal joint and distally with the metatarsophalangeal joint.
label: Metatarsal Bone Digit 2

description: The first and most medial of the five long bones located in the mid-foot, which articulates proximally with the medial cuneiform at the tarsometatarsal joint and distally with the metatarsophalangeal joint.
label: Metatarsal Bone Digit 1

description: Any one of the seven bones forming the instep of the foot.
label: Tarsal Bone

description: The irregular and largest tarsal bone that forms the heel.
label: Calcaneum

description: A bone on the lateral side of the tarsus between the calcaneus and the fourth and fifth metatarsal bones.
label: Cuboid Bone

description: One of three (medial, intermediate, or lateral cuneiform) bones in the foot medial to the cuboid bone and between either the first, second or third metatarsal bone and the navicular bone.
label: Cuneiform Bone of the Foot

description: The second wedge-shaped bone between the internal and external cuneiforms bones in the distal row of the tarsus.

description: The third or lateral wedge-shaped bone in the distal row of the tarsus.

description: The first or medial wedge-shaped bone in the distal row of the tarsus.

description: An oval-shaped bone of the tarsus found on the medial side of the foot.

description: The bone of the foot that connects with the tibia and fibula to form the ankle joint.

description: A bone of the toe.

description: A bone in the largest and most medial toe of the foot.

description: A bone in the second toe from the medial side of the foot.

description: A bone in the fourth toe from the medial side of the foot.

description: One of five small bones located in the foot, which form the base of each toe, and which articulates proximally with the head of a metatarsal bone.

description: A small flat triangular bone in front of the knee that articulates with the femur and protects the knee joint.

description: A bone of the arm (upper extremity).

description: The upper arm bone between the shoulder and elbow.

description: The long bone of the forearm that extends from the lateral aspect of the elbow to the thumb-side of the wrist.

description: One of the bones that comprise the forearm. The largest aspect articulates with the humerus at the elbow joint and the smallest portion of the ulna articulates with the carpal bones in the wrist.

description: One of the carpal, metacarpal, or phalangeal bones located in the hand.

description: Any of the small bones of the wrist joint, located between the radius and the ulna and the metacarpus.

description: The bone in the proximal row of carpal bones that lies between the scaphoid and triquetral bones.

description: A nut-shaped bone of the wrist located in the radial site of the hand. It is one of the eight carpal bones.

description: The medial bone of the proximal row of carpal bones.

description: The largest of eight carpal bones, located in the center of the hand.

description: A carpal bone on the thumb side of the hand that articulates with the 1st and 2nd metacarpals.

description: A carpal bone located between the lunate and pisiform bones.

description: A carpal bone located between the trapezium and capitate bones.

description: The medial bone in the distal row of carpal bones.

description: Any of the five bones between the wrist and the fingers that form the skeleton of the palm.

description: The fifth and the most lateral of five miniature long bones located in the palm of the hand, which articulates proximally with the hamate and fourth metacarpal at the carpometacarpal joint and distally with the small finger phalanx at the metacarpophalangeal joint.

description: The fourth of five miniature long bones located in the palm of the hand, which articulates proximally with the capitate, hamate, and third and fifth metacarpals at the carpometacarpal joint and distally with the ring finger phalanx at the metacarpophalangeal joint.
label: Metacarpal Bone Digit 4

description: The third of five miniature long bones located in the palm of the hand, which articulates proximally with the capitate and second and fourth metacarpals at the carpometacarpal joint and distally with the middle finger phalanx at the metacarpophalangeal joint.
label: Metacarpal Bone Digit 3

description: The second and the longest of five miniature long bones located in the palm of the hand, which articulates proximally with the trapezoid, trapezium, and capitate at the carpometacarpal joint and distally with the index finger phalanx at the metacarpophalangeal joint.
label: Metacarpal Bone Digit 2

description: The first and most medial of five miniature long bones located in the palm of the hand, which articulates proximally with the trapezium of the carpus at the carpometacarpal joint and distally with the thumb phalanx at the metacarpophalangeal joint.

description: A bone of the finger.

description: list()
label: Irregular Bone

description: A large irregular bone situated at the base and side of the skull, connected with the mandible via the temporomandibular joint. The temporal bone consists of the squamous, tympanic and petrous parts. The petrous portion of the temporal bone contains the vestibulocochlear organ of the inner ear.
label: Temporal Bone

description: A light and spongy bone that is cubical in shape. This bone is positioned at the anterior part of the cranium, sitting between the two orbits, at the roof of the nose. It consists of four parts: a horizontal or cribriform plate; a perpendicular plate; and two lateral masses or labyrinths.
label: Ethmoid Bone

description: A small bone located at the bottom of the spine. The coccyx is a result of 3-5 fused rudimentary vertebrae.
label: Coccyx

description: The lower jaw bone holding the lower teeth.

description: One of two strong processes of the sphenoid bone, which arise from the sides of the body, and are curved upward, laterally, and backward. The superior or cerebral surface of each greater wing forms part of the middle cranial fossa.

description: The butterfly-shaped bone located at the base of the skull that helps to form the orbit of the eye.

description: A supernumerary bone within the sutural joint of the skull.

description: The upper jawbone in vertebrates; it is fused to the cranium.

description: The largest of three pairs of conchae (superior, middle and inferior) located in the nasal cavity that is composed of spongy bony and a mucous membranes, which is highly vascular and semi-tumescent.

description: A U-shaped bone supporting the tongue. This bone is located at the base of the tongue and is suspended from the tips of the styloid processes of the temporal bones by the stylohyoid ligaments.

description: A horizontal bony plate located in the roof of the mouth created by the palatine processes of the two maxillae and the palatine bone.
label: Palate Bone

description: An irregularly shaped bone positioned at the back part of the nasal cavity between the maxilla and the pterygoid process of the sphenoid. It forms the posterior part of the hard palate and the lateral wall of the nasal fossa and helps to form the floor of the orbit as well as several adjoining parts.
label: Palatine Bone

description: One of the five bones of the spine that fuse to create the sacrum.

description: The triangular bone, made up of 5 fused bones of the spine, located in the lower area of the spine between the fifth lumbar vertebra and the coccyx.

description: The facial bone that forms the medial floor of the orbit.
